triples.evidence: Every vector is a point. That's right - a vector isn't just a list of numbers. It represents a location in space.

concepts.term: In general, if we're in n-dimensional space, the collection of all vectors of the same length - say, length r - forms an n-sphere.

evidence: If this vector has unit length - meaning its magnitude is one - then it lies on the unit circle.
